      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good high-level overview. To dig deeper for my review, I want to look at the data itself. Some critics of the systemic explanation argue that these disparities are simply a reflection of higher crime rates within specific demographic groups, implying the issue is behavioral rather than institutional. How does the academic literature address the tension between \"systemic bias\" arguments and the raw crime statistics that show higher frequencies of certain offenses in those communities?",
